# Nuvon Edit Command - 20 Usage Examples

## Basic Single File Editing

### 1. Add error handling to a single file
```bash
nuvon edit src/api.js "Add error handling to all fetch calls"
```

### 2. Update imports in a file
```bash
nuvon edit src/utils/helper.js "Update all CommonJS requires to ES6 imports"
```

### 3. Add JSDoc comments
```bash
nuvon edit src/services/user.js "Add comprehensive JSDoc comments to all functions"
```

### 4. Refactor variable names
```bash
nuvon edit src/components/Form.jsx "Rename all 'temp' variables to meaningful names based on their usage"
```

## Glob Pattern Matching

### 5. Update all test files to use Vitest
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.test.js" "Update all tests to use vitest instead of jest"
```

### 6. Add TypeScript types to all service files
```bash
nuvon edit "src/services/**/*.js" "Convert to TypeScript with proper type annotations"
```

### 7. Refactor console.logs across entire src directory
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.js" "Replace all console.logs with a logger utility from src/utils/logger"
```

### 8. Update all component PropTypes
```bash
nuvon edit "src/components/**/*.jsx" "Add PropTypes validation to all component exports"
```

## Package.json Management

### 9. Add a single package
```bash
nuvon edit package.json --add express
```

### 10. Add another package
```bash
nuvon edit package.json --add "react-router-dom"
```

## Dry Run and Preview

### 11. Preview changes without applying (dry-run)
```bash
nuvon edit src/utils/math.js --dry-run "Add input validation to all math functions"
```

### 12. Preview multiple file changes
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.js" --dry-run "Add error logging to all async functions"
```

## Auto-Confirm Changes

### 13. Auto-confirm all changes (no prompts)
```bash
nuvon edit src/config.js --yes "Update all configuration defaults for production"
```

### 14. Auto-confirm with dry-run to see what would happen
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.jsx" --yes --dry-run "Convert all class components to functional components"
```

## Backup and Recovery

### 15. Create backups before editing
```bash
nuvon edit src/database.js --backup "Refactor all database connection logic"
```

### 16. Edit multiple files with automatic backups
```bash
nuvon edit "src/models/**/*.js" --backup "Add database validation methods to all models"
```

## Undo Operations

### 17. Undo the last edit to a specific file
```bash
nuvon edit src/api.js --undo
```

### 18. Undo changes to a file in package.json
```bash
nuvon edit package.json --undo
```

## Complex Multi-File Operations

### 19. Refactor all components with backup and confirmation
```bash
nuvon edit "src/components/**/*.jsx" --backup "Add React hooks and remove class component logic"
```

### 20. Create new files with full instruction
```bash
nuvon edit "src/middleware/auth.js" --create "Create authentication middleware with JWT validation"
```

## Advanced Combinations

### Bonus Example 1: Full workflow with all options
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.js" --dry-run --backup "Add error handling, logging, and types"
```

### Bonus Example 2: Quick edit without confirmation
```bash
nuvon edit src/utils/validators.js --yes "Add comprehensive input validation"
```

### Bonus Example 3: Refactor entire codebase
```bash
nuvon edit "src/**/*.{js,jsx}" --backup --yes "Update all imports to use absolute paths"
```
